%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22'I%20almost%20died'%3A%20Mike%20Tyson%20after%20loss%20to%20Jake%20Paul%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731807017000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-115374974%2Cimgsize-56906.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fboxing%2Fi-almost-died-mike-tyson-after-loss-to-jake-paul%2Farticleshow%2F115374953.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Boxing%20legend%20Mike%20Tyson%2C%20despite%20losing%20to%20YouTube%20star%20Jake%20Paul%20in%20their%20heavyweight%20bout%2C%20expressed%20no%20regrets%20about%20stepping%20back%20into%20the%20ring.%20The%2058-year-old%20acknowledged%20Paul's%20agility%20and%20commended%20the%20experience%20of%20fighting%20in%20front%20of%20a%20packed%20Dallas%20Cowboys%20stadium.%20Final%20statistics%20revealed%20Tyson%20connected%20with%20just%2018%20of%2097%20punches%20thrown%2C%20while%20Paul%20threw%20278%20punches%20and%20landed%2078%20of%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fboxing%2Fi-almost-died-mike-tyson-after-loss-to-jake-paul%2Farticleshow%2F115374953.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20took%206%20months%20of%20leave%20after%20the%20birth%20of%20my%20first%20child.%20It%20was%20too%20long%20for%20me.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226163%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Little%20baby%20boy%20enjoying%20in%20mother's%20touch%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6734faf3fa0140cdd563286c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224622%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20(not%20pictured)%20felt%20financial%20stress%20because%20of%20how%20long%20her%20leave%20was.%3Cp%3Ehobo_018%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20I%20was%20pregnant%2C%20a%20childcare%20director%20recommended%20I%20take%20as%20much%20leave%20as%20possible.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20had%20four%20months%20of%20paid%20leave%20and%20negotiated%20two%20more%20months%20of%20unpaid%20leave.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20days%20were%20long%20and%20lonely%2C%20and%20I%20was%20stressed%20about%20our%20finances.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20expecting%20my%20first%20child%2C%20just%20starting%20my%20second%20trimester%2C%20when%20I%20received%20the%20advice.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20chatting%20on%20the%20phone%20with%20a%20local%20childcare%20director%2C%20inquiring%20about%20infant%20openings%20at%20her%20center%20and%20signing%20up%20for%20the%20waitlist.%20She%20told%20me%20to%20take%20as%20much%20parental%20leave%20as%20I%20could%20and%20that%20I%20would%20never%20regret%20doing%20so.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHer%20advice%20surprised%20me%20since%20her%20center%20offered%20spaces%20for%20infants%20as%20young%20as%20six%20weeks.%20Yet%2C%20as%20we%20talked%2C%20I%20learned%20her%20counsel%20stemmed%20from%20her%20feelings%20as%20a%20mother%20herself%20more%20so%20than%20her%20role%20as%20the%20center's%20director.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20followed%20her%20advice%20and%20regretted%20it.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225181fc8b-66f9-4ea6-937e-a93ac1285983%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20mixed%20paid%20and%20unpaid%20leave%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20had%20better-than-average%20vacation%20and%20disability%20policies%20where%20I%20worked%2C%20so%20I%20could%20take%20more%20than%20six%20weeks%20off%20after%20my%20baby%20arrived.%20The%20friends%20I%20knew%20who%20were%20already%20mothers%20advised%20me%20to%20take%20longer%20than%20the%20six%20or%2012%20weeks%20they%20had%20taken.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20I%20arranged%20to%20take%20as%20much%20leave%20as%20I%20could.%20I%20combined%20my%20disability%2C%20short-term%20sick%20pay%2C%20and%20accrued%20vacation%20time%2C%20some%20of%20which%20would%20run%20concurrently%20with%20my%20FMLA%20leave%2C%20for%20about%20four%20months%20of%20paid%20leave.%20Then%2C%20I%20negotiated%20that%20I'd%20return%20to%20work%20after%20an%20additional%20two%20months%20off%20unpaid%20while%20paying%20out-of-pocket%20for%20my%20family's%20healthcare%20coverage%20through%20COBRA.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20a%20lot%20to%20organize%20and%20set%20up%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20take%20as%20much%20leave%20as%20I%20could.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2292895a7e-9cc2-4d6f-a074-86b17b25c22c%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20lonely%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20few%20months%20after%20my%20son%20was%20born%20were%20a%20blur.%20I%20had%20many%20breastfeeding%20issues%20and%20struggled%20to%20overcome%20them%20while%20my%20body%20recovered%20from%20giving%20birth.%20The%20lack%20of%20sleep%20was%20challenging%20and%20stressful%2C%20too%2C%20as%20most%20new%20parents%20know.%20I%20was%20in%20awe%20of%20mothers%20who%20could%20%E2%80%94%20or%20had%20to%20%E2%80%94%20go%20back%20to%20work%20at%20six%20weeks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20I%20entered%20the%20third%20month%20of%20leave%2C%20my%20baby%20started%20to%20gain%20weight%2C%20and%20I%20gained%20confidence%20in%20my%20ability%20to%20feed%20him.%20Yet%20my%20days%20were%20long%20and%20lonely.%20My%20husband%20had%20gone%20back%20to%20work%20after%20the%20first%20week%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20family%20nearby%20since%20we%20had%20just%20moved%20to%20the%20area%20a%20few%20years%20earlier.%20Most%20of%20my%20friends%20were%20coworkers%20that%20I%20no%20longer%20saw%20daily.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20ventured%20out%20into%20my%20community%2C%20joining%20playgroups%20and%20taking%20infant%20classes.%20But%20some%20were%20expensive.%20Or%20they%20lasted%20only%20an%20hour%20or%20two%20each%20week%2C%20which%20was%20not%20enough%20time%20for%20me%20to%20develop%20true%20friendships%20with%20other%20caregivers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20felt%20guilty%20that%20I%20had%20a%20lengthy%20leave%20that%20so%20many%20other%20parents%20would%20have%20coveted.%20I%20thought%20I%20should%20be%20fueled%20by%20love%20and%20appreciation%20for%20this%20time%20with%20my%20baby.%20But%20while%20I%20felt%20intense%20love%20for%20my%20child%2C%20most%20days%2C%20I%20was%20lonely%20and%20exhausted%20by%20new%20motherhood.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22015fa2b1-ccdb-4ac6-b1f0-8730c54c5486%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20stressed%20about%20our%20finances%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20last%20couple%20of%20months%20of%20my%20leave%20presented%20financial%20stress%20on%20top%20of%20my%20feelings%20of%20isolation.%20Now%2C%20I%20had%20no%20income%20and%20was%20paying%20a%20substantial%20amount%20out%20of%20pocket%20to%20ensure%20my%20family's%20benefits%20continued%20until%20I%20went%20back%20to%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20I%20navigated%20that%20first%20day%20back%2C%20which%20turned%20into%20the%20first%20week%20and%20then%20the%20first%20month%2C%20I%20was%20struck%20by%20how%20stimulated%20and%20happy%20I%20felt.%20My%20loneliness%20melted%20away%20as%20I%20was%20not%20only%20surrounded%20by%20co-workers%20but%20also%20supported%20in%20parenting%20by%20the%20teachers%20and%20other%20parents%20I%20started%20developing%20relationships%20with%20at%20the%20daycare%20center.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20had%20my%20second%20child%20three%20years%20later%2C%20I%20did%20not%20take%20all%20the%20time%20that%20I%20could.%20I%20took%20four%20months%2C%20which%20was%20just%20right%20for%20me.%20I%20had%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20to%20physically%20recover%20and%20adjust%20to%20life%20with%20a%20newborn%2C%20plus%20a%20couple%20more%20months%20to%20bond%20with%20my%20baby.%20This%20time%20I%20surrounded%20myself%20with%20the%20mom%20friends%20I'd%20made%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years%20and%20I%20was%20more%20confident%20in%20my%20parenting%20abilities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20mental%20health%20was%20better%20during%20a%20four-month%20leave%20versus%20six.%20I%20think%20it%20was%20the%20best%20amount%20of%20leave%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20the%20most%20amount%20of%20leave%2C%20for%20me%20and%20my%20family.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftook-six-months-parental-leave-too-long-stress-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731806821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6734fba6ede4eeae39274061%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftook-six-months-parental-leave-too-long-stress-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20took%20a%20combination%20of%20paid%20and%20unpaid%20leave%20with%20my%20first%20child.%20I%20felt%20isolated%20and%20was%20stressed%20about%20our%20finances.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Katy%20M.%20Clark)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftook-six-months-parental-leave-too-long-stress-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Does%20Africa%20need%20to%20embrace%20AI%20to%20keep%20its%20music%20centre%20stage%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731806011000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2Fc7f8%2Flive%2F500b0fb0-8c71-11ef-b6b0-c9af5f7f16e4.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcdenplz5j89o%234%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20pioneers%20see%20it%20as%20opportunity%20but%20others%20fear%20the%20continent's%20creativity%20will%20be%20stripped%20for%20profit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcdenplz5j89o%22%