20is%20%26quot%3Bvery%20important%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20UK%20and%20Japan%2C%20%26quot%3Bparticularly%2C%20as%20we%20see%2C%20a%20rising%20threat%20of%20China%20taking%20place%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20conversation%2C%20the%20former%20British%20prime%20minister%20took%20a%20critical%20view%20of%20the%20European%20economy%20and%20said%20%26quot%3Bour%20continent%20is%20sinking%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECiting%20the%20GDP%20per%20capita%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20she%20lamented%20that%20it%20is%20below%20the%20corresponding%20figure%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETruss%20also%20said%20some%20arrangement%20in%20the%20British%20bureaucracy%20%26quot%3Bneeds%20to%20be%20fixed%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20she%20would%20like%20to%20see%20the%20%26quot%3Bbest%20of%20reforms%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20what%20I%20am%20interested%20in%2C%20how%20can%20we%20create%20that%20movement%2C%20a%20bit%20like%20the%20'MAGA'%20movement%20or%20the%20tea-party%20movement%20in%20the%20US%20that%20led%20to%20the%20big%20changes%20we%20are%20seeing.%20Frankly%2C%20I%20think%20we%20need%20a%20British%20Trump.%20The%20question%20is%20who%20that%20individual%20might%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20by%20the%20host%20whether%20she%20would%20want%20to%20play%20that%20role%2C%20the%20former%20prime%20minister%20gave%20a%20response%20with%20a%20dry%20sense%20of%20humour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20already%20put%20my%20fingers%20in%20the%20fire%20and%20had%20them%20severely%20burnt%2C%20but%20that%20is%20the%20type%20of%20approach%20that%20we%20now%20need%20to%20get%20the%20change%20in%20Britain%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20the%20people%20of%20the%20UK%20want%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bsame%20kind%20of%20revolution%20that%20Trump%20is%20delivering%20in%20America%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20is%20actually%20taking%20on%20the%20left-wing%20establishment%2C%20giving%20more%20power%20to%20people%2C%20giving%20more%20opportunities%20to%20businesses%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20run%20a%20successful%20enterprise%2C%20Truss%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20we%20have%20a%20very%20powerful%20bureaucracy%20that%20wants%20to%20keep%20us%20attached%20to%20Europe%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20does%20not%20want%20the%20UK%20to%20sign%20trade%20deals%20with%20the%20US%20or%20India%20and%20wants%20to%20continue%20this%20status%20quo.%20That%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bbattle%26quot%3B%20that%20is%20still%20going%20on%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20Truss%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20wants%20to%20see%20the%20UK%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20dump%20EU%20regulations%26quot%3B%20and%20sign%20trade%20deals%20with%20countries%20like%20India%20and%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20conversation%2C%20Truss%20praised%20the%20return%20of%20Trump%20to%20the%20White%20House%20several%20times%2C%20as%20also%20India's%20growing%20role%20on%20the%20world%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20she%20feels%20that%20under%20President%20Trump%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20are%20seeing%20a%20revival%20of%20US%20strengths%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETruss%20said%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20she%20was%20on%20record%20praising%20the%20fact%20that%20Trump%20had%20won%20the%20US%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20is%20all%20set%20to%20be%20sworn%20in%20at%20an%20inauguration%20ceremony%20scheduled%20to%20be%20held%20in%20January%20after%20his%20resounding%20victory%20in%20the%20US%20presidential%20election%20in%20November.%20This%20will%20be%20his%20second%20term%20in%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Trump%20revolution%20that%20we%20are%20seeing%20in%20the%20US%2C%20is%20coming%20to%20Europe.%20You%20can%20see%20the%20dissatisfaction%20in%20France%2C%20and%20Germany%20with%20economic%20stagnation.%20That%20dissatisfaction%20is%20coming%20to%20Europe%2C%20so%20you%20are%20going%20to%