T%20N-2%2C%20into%20orbit%20on%20a%20Falcon%209%20rocket%20for%20the%20first%20time%20next%20week.%20The%20rocket%20is%20made%20by%20SpaceX%2C%20the%20company%20owned%20by%20'The%20First%20Buddy'%20of%20US%20President-Elect%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20Elon%20Musk.%20However%2C%20the%20question%20that%20looms%20is%20-%20how%20reliable%20is%20this%20American%20rocket%20and%20could%20India%20have%20used%20another%20launcher%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFalcon%209%20is%20a%20partially%20reusable%20rocket%20made%20by%20billionaire%20Elon%20Musk's%20SpaceX%20and%20it%20had%20its%20first%20flight%20of%20the%20current%20version%20in%202018.%20To%20date%2C%20the%20rocket%20has%20been%20part%20of%20393%20launches%20and%20has%20faced%20just%20four%20failures%2C%20achieving%20a%20remarkable%20success%20rate%20of%2099%20percent.%20A%20dedicated%20launch%20of%20a%20Falcon%209%20rocket%20costs%20about%20%2470%20million%20on%20average%2C%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20got%20a%20good%20deal%20on%20this%20maiden%20launch%20with%20SpaceX%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Radhakrishnan%20Durairaj%2C%20Chairman%20and%20Managing%20Director%20of%20New%20Space%20India%20Limited%2C%20the%20commercial%20arm%20of%20the%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%20that%20is%20spearheading%20this%20satellite%20launch.%20Falcon%209%20was%20the%20only%20commercial%20launcher%20available%20for%20India%20for%20the%20time%20frame%20ISRO%20was%20seeking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20standard%20Falcon%209%20rocket%20is%2070%20meters%20high%20and%20weighs%20around%20549%20tons%20at%20lift-off.%20It%20is%20designed%20as%20a%20two-stage%20rocket%20that%20can%20lift%20up%20to%208%2C300%20kilograms%20to%20the%20geosynchronous%20transfer%20orbit%20(GTO)%20and%2022%2C800%20kilograms%20to%20the%20low%20earth%20orbit%20(LEO).%20It%20can%20also%20carry%20nearly%204%2C000%20kilograms%20to%20the%20orbit%20of%20Mars.%20The%20GSAT%20N-2%20satellite%2C%20which%20the%20rocket%20is%20supposed%20to%20carry%2C%20has%20a%20mass%20of%204%2C700%20kilograms.%20India%20has%20sought%20a%20dedicated%20launch%20of%20the%20rocket%20and%20there%20will%20be%20no%20co-passenger%20satellites%20on%20this%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20key%20features%20of%20SpaceX's%20Falcon%209%20is%20that%20it%20is%20a%20reusable%20rocket%20designed%20for%20reliable%20and%20safe%20transport%20of%20people%20and%20payloads%20into%20the%20Earth's%20orbit%20and%20beyond.%20It%20is%20also%20the%20world's%20first%20orbital-class%20reusable%20rocket.%20This%20allows%20SpaceX%20to%20re-fly%20the%20most%20expensive%20parts%20of%20the%20rocket%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20drives%20down%20the%20cost%20of%20space%20access.%20It%20is%20fuelled%20by%20rocket-grade%20kerosene%20and%20liquefied%20oxygen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Falcon%209%20rocket%20has%20had%20324%20re-flights%2C%20which%20means%20rockets%20with%20reusable%20parts.%20From%20its%20many%20missions%2C%20it%20has%20had%20349%20landings%20of%20the%20stages.%20The%20first%20stage%20of%20the%20rocket%20returns%20to%20its%20base%20after%20it%20completes%20its%20job%2C%20which%20makes%20for%20a%20spectacular%20viewing.%20To%20date%2C%20the%20maximum%20a%20stage%20has%20been%20reused%20is%2023%20times.%20This%2C%20SpaceX%20says%2C%20helps%20lower%20the%20cost%20of%20launches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-media-max-width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ETracking%20footage%20of%20Falcon%209%20first%20stage%20returning%20to%20Earth%20after%20launching%20the%20Ax-2%20mission%20to%20orbit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FfLPQ7OhJOg%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FfLPQ7OhJOg%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20SpaceX%20(%40SpaceX)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSpaceX%2Fstatus%2F1664832049516097537%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJune%203%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Falcon%209%20set%20a%20world%20record%20by%20launching%20143%20satellites%20into%20orbit%20on%20a%20single%20mission%2C%20breaking%20India's%202017%20record%20of%20launching%20104%20satellites%20on%20a%20single%20mission%20of%20the%20Polar%20Satellite%20Launch%20Vehicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%20alone%2C%20SpaceX%20has%20already%20had%20106%20Falcon%209%20launches%20and%20the%20company%20aims%20to%20complete%20a%20total%20of%20148%20launches%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20which%20would%20be%20a%20record%20for%20any%20single%20rocket.%20In%20fact%2C%20within%20this%20week%20itself%2C%20there%20are%20four%20scheduled%20launches%20of%20the%20Falcon%209%20rocket%20from%20three%20different%20launch%20sites.%20In%20comparison%2C%20ISRO%20has%20made%2095%20launches%20in%20the%20last%2045%20years%20since%20India%20began%20launching%20heavier%20rockets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20Falcon%209%20rocket%20is%20also%20used%20for%20undertaking%20orbital%20missions%20to%20supply%20cargo%20and%20fly%20astronauts%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS).%20The%20rocket%20has%20carried%20SpaceX's%20Dragon%20spacecraft%20on%2020%20missions%20to%20the%20ISS%2C%20out%20of%20which%2C%20the%20most%20talked%20about%20is%20the%20Crew%20Dragon%20mission%20launched%20on%20September%2028%2C%202024%2C%20aimed%20to%20bring%20back%20astronauts%20Sunita%20Williams%20and%20Butch%20Wilmore%20from%20the%20ISS.%20They%20will%20return%20to%20Earth%20in%20February%202025%20on%20the%20Crew%20Dragon%20module.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731764280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fuvu0tpng_falcon-9-rocket_625x300_16_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmusks-falcon-9-rocket-which-will-carry-indian-satellite-has-99-success-rate-7034619%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20is%20all%20set%20to%20launch%20its%20most%20sophisticated%20broadband%20communications%20satellite%20GSAT-20%2C%20also%20called%20GSAT%20N-2%2C%20into%20orbit%20on%20a%20Fa