e.%20As%20a%20homeowner%2C%20you'll%20benefit%20from%20these%20increases%20since%20they%20add%20to%20your%20equity.%20But%20if%20you%20wait%20to%20buy%20a%20home%2C%20you'll%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20higher%20prices%20when%20you%20decide%20to%20buy%20later%20on.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ERent%20increases%20over%20time%2C%20but%20mortgage%20payments%20can%20be%20fixed%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20rent%2C%20your%20housing%20costs%20can%20go%20up%20every%20time%20you%20renew%20your%20lease.%20If%20you%20buy%20a%20house%20using%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwhat-is-fixed-rate-mortgage%5C%22%3Efixed-rate%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20your%20monthly%20payment%20will%20stay%20the%20same%20for%20the%20entire%20time%20you%20have%20your%20mortgage%20(though%20your%20taxes%20and%20insurance%20can%20go%20up%20over%20time).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHomeownership%20isn't%20for%20everyone%2C%20and%20you%20should%20only%20buy%20when%20you're%20ready%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20pros%20and%20cons%20to%20both%20buying%20and%20renting%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20one-size-fits-all%20answer%20to%20whether%20you%20should%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Frenting-vs-buying-house-pros-cons%5C%22%3Ebuy%20or%20rent%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20do%20want%20to%20own%20a%20home%20one%20day%20but%20aren't%20sure%20how%20to%20start%20preparing%2C%20one%20of%20the%20best%20things%20you%20can%20do%20now%20is%20make%20sure%20you%20have%20a%20solid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%3Eemergency%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20set%20aside.%20Canna%20says%20you%20should%20have%20six%20months%20of%20living%20expenses%20saved%20up%20in%20your%20emergency%20fund%20before%20you%20start%20saving%20for%20a%20down%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20also%20want%20to%20see%20if%20you%20qualify%20for%20any%2